# Testing & Quality

## Before marking work done

Run when relevant:

```bash
npm run typecheck   # or tsc --noEmit if configured
npm run lint
npm run build
npm test            # when test runner exists
```

## Critical scenarios (test or document manual checks)

- **Workspace isolation** — user A cannot read/write workspace B data
- **Contact identity matching** — match on channel id, not name; no unsafe auto-merge
- **Duplicate message prevention** — same external message id does not create duplicate rows
- **Status changes** — pipeline transitions update follow-up lists correctly
- **Appointment / session package logic** — completion deducts sessions; no over-deduction

If automated tests are not available yet, add a **Manual checks** section to the worklog entry describing what was verified.

Reference: `docs/11-testing-strategy.md`
